		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">And is SSOR95 the best sample/SPC ripper?</div><br />Of course not ! I have to point you to the tool I wrote : <a href="http://www.romhacking.net/utilities/681/" class="postlink">BRRTools</a>. There is a SPC sample ripper included, the only thing is that you have to specify a range, for example if you want to rip from 0 to 7 you'd have to use -f0 -l7 (first = 0, last = 7) as arguments to the command line.<br />SNESSor is still better when it comes to ripping directly from ROMs though.<br /><br />Also just wait 1 year or 2 so I can write the MML compiler and SPC music engine I've always wanted to write for like 10 years, and you'll be able to compose SNES music without the limitations of MOD/XM whatever.

		

